  "title": "IT Specialist",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><ul><li>Plan, set up, and manage all IT and network infrastructure for new store openings, including computers, printers, mobile devices, CCTV systems, Wi-Fi, and telephone lines.</li><li>Coordinate, supervise, and manage external vendors for IT and technical setup works.</li><li>Set up and manage new user email accounts, including account creation, configuration, access rights assignment, and ongoing maintenance.<br /><br />Manage and maintain all IT server, systems, hardware, software, and networks across the group of companies.</li><li>Ensure all outlets’ CCTV systems and IT equipment are fully operational at all times.</li><li>Provide day-to-day technical support to users, including troubleshooting hardware, software, and network issues.</li><li>Perform daily maintenance of PCs, laptops, and server rooms, including system updates and checks. Monitor, manage, and maintain network infrastructure such as routers, switches, firewalls, and VPNs.</li><li>Ensure IT security through proper data backups, antivirus management, system access control, and security best practices.</li><li>Manage system configurations, user access rights, and conduct regular access reviews.</li><li>Assist in developing, reviewing, and implementing IT policies, SOPs, and IT guidelines.</li><li>Monitor, log, track, and resolve IT incidents, escalating issues when necessary and ensuring closure.</li><li>Research, evaluate, and recommend IT equipment and solutions; obtain quotations and support procurement processes.</li><li>Evaluate and recommend new technologies to improve operational efficiency and system reliability.</li><li>Perform ad-hoc IT duties as assigned by Management.</li></ul></p><p></p>",
